task.en: Where is the source data of the two charts? Help me find that data table, and copy the source data table to an empty Pages document.
task.zh: 这两个图表对应的源数据在哪里？帮我找到那个数据表，并复制到一个空白的Pages文稿中。
task.ar: أين توجد البيانات المصدرية لهذين المخططين؟ ساعدني في العثور على جدول البيانات، ونسخ جدول البيانات المصدر إلى مستند Pages فارغ.
task.ja: この2つのチャートのソースデータはどこにありますか？そのデータテーブルを見つけて、空白のPagesドキュメントにコピーしてください。
task.ru: Где находятся исходные данные для этих двух диаграмм? Помогите мне найти эту таблицу данных и скопируйте ее в пустой документ Pages.

pre_command.en: osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Keynote" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to activate' && sleep 5 && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to make new document with properties {document template:template "Personal Budget"}'
pre_command.zh: osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Keynote" to quit without saving' && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to activate' && sleep 5 && osascript -e 'tell application "Numbers" to make new document with properties {document template:template "个人预算"}'

grading_command: osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to count rows of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "11" && osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to count columns of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "4" && osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to get value of cell "B2" of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "200" && osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to get value of cell "C3" of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "32" && osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to get value of cell "D5" of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "50" && osascript -e 'tell application "Pages" to get value of cell "C11" of table 1 of front document' 2>/dev/null | grep -q "1202.75" && echo "True" || echo "False"
